# Cursor Rules for EcoPro Platform

**IMPORTANT: Before starting ANY coding task, read `/docs/AGENTS.md` first!**

## Critical Rules

1. NEVER create a local database - Only use the Render database
2. NEVER ask the user to do anything - You are the one who does everything
3. Read /docs/AGENTS.md before coding - It contains all platform specifics
4. Read /docs/PLATFORM_OVERVIEW.md for architecture

## Project Structure

- Server: /server/ (Node.js + Express, port 8080)
- Client: /client/ (Vite + React, port 5173)
- Database: PostgreSQL on Render (NEVER local)
- Docs: /docs/ (READ THESE FIRST)

## Authentication

- JWT tokens with role/user_type fields
- Admin: role='admin' OR user_type='admin'
- Client: user_type='client'
- Always check both role AND user_type fields

## Before Any Task

1. Read /docs/AGENTS.md
2. Understand existing code patterns
3. Test thoroughly
4. Don't break existing features
